1
00:00:01,870 --> 00:00:04,540
Episode 10

2
00:00:05,990 --> 00:00:13,070
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

3
00:00:14,630 --> 00:00:17,970
This place is really in the middle of nowhere.

4
00:00:17,970 --> 00:00:20,740
To think that this was where he spent his last moments.

5
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:25,140
It was a hit and run.

6
00:00:27,740 --> 00:00:30,330
It was raining hard that day.

7
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:36,370
It was a truck that was making deliveries near that area.

8
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:39,840
Four hours after the accident, the driver turned himself in.

9
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,840
Because the streams of rain were so heavy,

10
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:45,590
he testified to the police that he didn't know he had hit Ian.

11
00:00:45,590 --> 00:00:50,950
When he woke up from sleeping at a rest stop, he found blood on his vehicle, so he went to the police station.

12
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:54,120
After getting the call, I rushed to the hospital morgue.

13
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:57,890
It was the last time I saw him, dead and covered in blood.

14
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,700
Do you know what I regret the most right now?

15
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:05,330
There is something you regret?

16
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:34,920
Ian! What do I do?

17
00:01:45,420 --> 00:01:49,210
I'm sorry.  I'm sorry, Ian.

18
00:01:53,630 --> 00:01:56,160
While he was alive, not once did I...

19
00:01:56,690 --> 00:02:01,860
I never held his hand even once, except for when he was little.

20
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:05,550
I see.

21
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:09,170
I didn't know that it was a hit and run.

22
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,400
Ian was hit by a truck on this road,

23
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:15,370
And Ian's car was found on a vacant lot nearby.

24
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:20,540
Why did he leave his car and walk down this road?

25
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:23,690
Last time, you said that the person he loved killed him.

26
00:02:23,690 --> 00:02:27,440
So I thought that he was riding in the car that his girlfriend was driving,

27
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:30,910
and that's how the accident happened.

28
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:43,400
His girlfriend was found in another location the next day.  In a confused state.

29
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,830
What?

30
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:49,560
Does that mean they were in this location together?

31
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,060
Yes.

32
00:02:51,060 --> 00:02:53,250
I don't really understand.

33
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:56,540
Then were they together and then fought and separated?

34
00:02:58,270 --> 00:03:01,740
I wonder what happened that day?

35
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:04,740
You should have looked into it.

36
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:07,700
Do you think that I didn't look into it?

37
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:08,720
That's not what I'm saying.

38
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:11,730
I want to know more than anyone what happened that day.

39
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:16,430
To you, he may be just another person you can't remember,

40
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:19,310
But to me, he's the most important person.

41
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:21,990
Do you know what Ian was like when he was discovered?

42
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:27,630
He was practically in two pieces.

43
00:03:28,330 --> 00:03:30,470
Eight of his ribs were broken.

44
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:34,400
They punctured his intestine, splintered his spleen, and ruptured his liver.

45
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,030
That's enough!

46
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:41,230
Please stop.

47
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:43,090
I'm not blaming you.

48
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:47,460
You said that the girlfriend is alive and well, so you can go ask her.

49
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:50,390
About what happened that day.

50
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:59,270
Is there a special reason why you can't ask?

51
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:03,250
A special reason why I can't ask?

52
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:07,470
She had no memory?  She can't remember anything that happened that day?

53
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:09,830
Are you serious?

54
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,970
What are you going to accomplish by meeting someone who doesn't remember?

55
00:04:15,970 --> 00:04:19,070
We don't even know for sure if that woman was at the scene.

56
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:21,760
Her bag was in the car!

57
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,640
Hyung, you don't know how Ian died?  He died because of his abdominal organs ruptured.

58
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:29,580
His liver was stabbed by a knife!  But you still think it's a simple hit and run?

59
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:32,960
So you think now that the woman killed Ian?

60
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:36,110
I can't say that's not true.  Since she could be pretending not to remember.

61
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,240
What?

62
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:40,640
I'll find out what the truth is.

63
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:44,560
Isn't Hong Yi Yeong the only person who witnessed the events of that day?

64
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:47,670
Ian is dead, but that woman is still alive.

65
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:55,620
I don't know who his girlfriend is or where she lives.

66
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:59,210
The police won't tell me her identity.

67
00:05:00,490 --> 00:05:03,430
I didn't know he was dating anyone in the first place.

68
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:08,030
I see.

69
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:26,370
You're not mad, are you?

70
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:32,090
Earlier, my emotions got the better  of me. I'm sorry.

71
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,350
It's fine.  I'm more sorry.

72
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:39,370
I don't even know anything, yet I asked an unnecessary question.

73
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,530
Where is the location of your accident?

74
00:05:45,530 --> 00:05:47,000
Excuse me?

75
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,550
You said that you had an accident in a taxi.

76
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:54,060
I heard I was on the way to Professor Song's place,

77
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:58,170
so probably on the road from Seoul to Yongin?

78
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:06,510
Wait a minute, wait a minute.  Please stop the car for a minute.

79
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:29,860
Who are you? Who are you?

80
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:38,900
Is this place familiar?

81
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:42,240
It somehow felt familiar.

82
00:06:42,890 --> 00:06:45,040
When were you in this warehouse?

83
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:54,750
A dream? I feels as if I saw it in a dream.

84
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:05,290
Let's go in. If you go in, you might remember something.

85
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,790
Calm down!

86
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,730
What is it?  What?

87
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,760
No! No!

88
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:36,960
Please open the door.  There's a person in here, please open the door!

89
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:39,380
Please open the door!

90
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:45,030
Help! Save me, please!

91
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,320
Please open the door.

92
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,270
Calm down, it's okay.

93
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:50,300
Save me!

94
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:54,550
Please help me!

95
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:34,360
I'm back.

96
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:37,020
Oh, you're back early, even though you had a work dinner.

97
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:39,360
I didn't want to go, so I just came here.

98
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,840
Father isn't here?

99
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:43,230
He went on a delivery.

100
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:48,840
Hey, call Yi Yeong.  She hasn't been answering her phone since earlier.

101
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,960
Why, Yi Yeong?  Is there something wrong?

102
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:58,250
What do you mean, is there something wrong?  I was going to tell her that I wanted to set her up on a blind date.

103
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:00,440
Do you think she already figured that out?

104
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:03,540
That blind date. Don't you see my crutches?

105
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:06,620
Do you know how much I'm suffering because of your blind dates?

106
00:10:06,620 --> 00:10:09,140
This girl, who do you think you're screaming at?

107
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:11,340
Hurry up and call Yi Yeong.

108
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:14,820
When I can't get in touch with her, I can't even eat because I get worried.

109
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,120
I understand.

110
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:26,000
Unni

111
00:10:35,050 --> 00:10:39,920
I reported it to 911 and the local police station, so someone should be here soon.

112
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,050
Are you better?

113
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,910
No.

114
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:49,290
Why were you so scared?  Did you really have a memory of being here before?

115
00:10:49,290 --> 00:10:51,710
I'm not sure.

116
00:10:52,570 --> 00:10:56,970
I kept seeing the scary images from my dreams.

117
00:10:56,970 --> 00:10:58,920
What kinds of scenes?

118
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:09,310
I'm not sure.

119
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:11,600
I can't tell what.

120
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:17,600
Calm down.

121
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:38,840
It's okay.

122
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,430
Nothing will happen. It's okay.

123
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:02,010
Should I make you laugh in just ten seconds?

124
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:06,400
How?

125
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:08,420
Wait and see.

126
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:23,470
♫ Following a long shadow

127
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:31,550
♫ I'm walking with you in the darkness of twilight

128
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:40,230
♫ Holding hands, even if it forever,

129
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:48,560
♫ just being together makes me cry.

130
00:12:58,030 --> 00:13:04,250
♫  Winter is approaching

131
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:51,180
♫ I'm not the only one weak.

132
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:55,860
♫ I love you like this and

133
00:13:55,860 --> 00:14:01,430
♫ It's the only thing my heart can do.

134
00:14:01,430 --> 00:14:08,340
♫ The only thing it can do.

135
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,610
You laughed, right?

136
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:22,220
Its so funny that I'm tearing up.

137
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:25,430
- I've been wanting to tell you for awhile...
- Yes?

138
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:28,370
You're really bad at singing.

139
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:30,330
You know, right?

140
00:14:30,330 --> 00:14:32,660
That's so unexpected.

141
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:36,100
I told you that my specialty is singing badly.

142
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:39,690
But wasn't I kind of good today?

143
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:43,200
I'm doing all sorts of things after meeting you.

144
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:50,910
♫ Being with you is like walking through a green forest ♫

145
00:14:50,910 --> 00:14:56,100
♫ I can't never get tired ♫

146
00:14:56,100 --> 00:15:02,560
♫ It's okay even once in a while if your voice is soft ♫

147
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:06,250
What's the reason?

148
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,730
That you are able to sleep when you hear out-of-tune singing?

149
00:15:07,730 --> 00:15:11,070
♫ So that I can love you more ♫

150
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:12,990
♫ For a long time ♫

151
00:15:12,990 --> 00:15:15,870
I'm not sure why.

152
00:15:15,870 --> 00:15:22,780
When I listen to it, for some strange reason, I feel at peace.

153
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:24,730
Especially your singing.

154
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:29,350
To me, it's a magical voice, like an angel.

155
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,110
The person who made the report, are you inside?

156
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:38,870
Yes, we're inside, here!

157
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:40,560
Quickly.

158
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:45,310
Are you alright? You're not hurt anywhere?

159
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:46,570
Yes, we're alright.

160
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:50,590
The warehouse custodian didn't know that anyone was inside and locked the door.

161
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:54,200
He's elderly, so he must not have heard you asking him to open the door.

162
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,020
Here, please come out.

163
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:26,820
Come in.

164
00:16:39,310 --> 00:16:43,220
What are you doing here at this time?  Did you drink?

165
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:45,520
I drank.

166
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:49,850
I can't even play my instrument, so I was just going to drink myself to death.

167
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:55,000
Wait here. I'll take you home.

168
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:05,980
Are you drunk?

169
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:08,430
Do you know how many security cameras there are here?

170
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:12,480
I don't know, and I don't care.

171
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:16,190
It would be better if someone saw us.

172
00:17:16,190 --> 00:17:17,880
You're not even a child.

173
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,620
Wait here. I'll be back quickly.

174
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:47,100
Is it alright if I don't get out?

175
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:50,910
I wonder why you're acting so child-like today.

176
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:53,820
Come on, quickly.

177
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:10,880
Don't drink so much.  Alcohol is not good when there's an infection.

178
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,840
Do I need to tell you that?

179
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:17,120
Leave some time free tomorrow.  I'll take you to a hospital that I go to.

180
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:23,830
I don't want to go home.  Can't you stay with me tonight?

181
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:29,220
Of course not.

182
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:35,960
Sleep well, and don't wake up.

183
00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:50,420
I saw you that day, Conductor.

184
00:18:51,770 --> 00:18:53,300
What are you suddenly talking about?

185
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:59,620
That day. One year ago, when we performed with Kim Ian.

186
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,480
What did you see that day?

187
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:10,990
You didn't go to the afterparty, you turned off your cellphone, and I saw you go somewhere.

188
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:17,410
By chance, did you meet Kim Ian that night?

189
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:30,100
Why would I meet Kim Ian?

190
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:37,420
Then, is it a coincidence that Kim Ian died that night in an accident?

191
00:19:38,140 --> 00:19:42,140
If it's not a coincidence, are you saying that I killed him?

192
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:45,430
What kind of person do you think I am?

193
00:19:45,430 --> 00:19:48,240
You're going to say anything just because I didn't let you play?

194
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:51,240
I'm just worried about you.

195
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,180
Worried about what?

196
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:55,230
I told you that I saw Hong Yi Yeong riding in Kim Ian's car.

197
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:58,150
As soon as you heard that, you disappeared somewhere.

198
00:19:58,150 --> 00:20:01,090
Kim Ian died, and Hong Yi Yeong can't remember anything.

199
00:20:01,090 --> 00:20:05,230
You keep paying attention to her. How could I not be worried?

200
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:07,410
I keep thinking you were swept into something bad—

201
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:11,840
Get rid of those useless worries. I went home and slept that night.

202
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:15,050
Don't you remember how hard I worked for three months for that performance?

203
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:19,200
I don't know why I have to explain myself to you like this.

204
00:21:06,190 --> 00:21:08,340
Thanks.

205
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:12,200
Hong Yi Yeong!

206
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:15,500
Unni?

207
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:20,110
My mom and I must have called you more than ten times between us. Do you know how dangerous this world is?

208
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:22,390
Am I a kid?

209
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:25,150
You came to my house just because I didn't pick up?

210
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:26,590
With that leg.

211
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:28,070
How long have you known my mother?

212
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:31,240
If I hadn't said I'd come she would've called the cops.

213
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:34,020
Check your phone every once in a while!

214
00:21:34,020 --> 00:21:36,730
Okay.

215
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:38,570
Here, tea.

216
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:49,330
Where did you go with Jang Yun? You used to talk about him being a stalker.

217
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:51,730
I said he's not a stalker.

218
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:58,870
Unni, do you remember a pianist who was in an accident last summer?

219
00:21:58,870 --> 00:22:01,860
His name was Kim Ian.

220
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:05,890
Kim Ian? I think I heard of him before.

221
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:07,730
What about him?

222
00:22:07,730 --> 00:22:10,000
Jang Yun is his older brother.

223
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,160
What?

224
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:17,270
I think it was because of my accident last year. I have no memory of Kim Ian at all.

225
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:21,130
I said I wanted to find my memories, and Jang Yun said he woul help me.

226
00:22:21,130 --> 00:22:24,700
So we went to a place where I might remember him.

227
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:28,490
Ah, it's cold!

228
00:22:46,670 --> 00:22:50,180
Unknown Caller

229
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:03,850
Who could it be?

230
00:23:03,850 --> 00:23:05,110
Hello?

231
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:08,150
♫ Goodbye yellow brick road ♫

232
00:23:08,150 --> 00:23:11,810
♫ Where the dogs of society howl ♫

233
00:23:11,810 --> 00:23:16,940
Hello? Who is it?
♫ You can't plant me in your penthouse ♫

234
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:47,210
Did something happen? What about your cousin?

235
00:23:47,210 --> 00:23:50,720
She gave me medicine and left.

236
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:57,590
Is it okay if I come in? It's a bit scary to be at home alone.

237
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,390
Sure.

238
00:24:03,390 --> 00:24:05,350
I'm sorry.

239
00:24:12,770 --> 00:24:14,670
Want something to drink?

240
00:24:14,670 --> 00:24:16,070
Thank you.

241
00:24:16,070 --> 00:24:18,800
Has something like this happened before?

242
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:21,180
No, this is the first time.

243
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:24,030
Call me immediately if it happens again.

244
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:26,130
I will.

245
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:31,180
What is it?

246
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:33,190
No, just...

247
00:24:33,190 --> 00:24:37,470
I just haven't sat here and admired your home before.

248
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:43,830
When you first moved next door, I thought you were a weird person.

249
00:24:45,490 --> 00:24:47,950
I heard you thought I was a stalker.

250
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,970
That happened, too.

251
00:24:54,720 --> 00:25:00,440
A lot of stuff happened. I got really mad yesterday.

252
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:05,600
To be honest, it's not that I have nothing to be anxious about.

253
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:10,250
Looking back, I think it was a relief.

254
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:14,990
That you came here, so close to me.

255
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:30,590
Can you please play piano a bit for me?

256
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:35,280
It's not common to see such an expensive piano in this neighborhood.

257
00:25:46,230 --> 00:25:49,100
Oh, you're here? Come in.

258
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:56,090
It's been a while, our star conductor.

259
00:25:56,090 --> 00:26:00,980
No matter how popular as you are, what can I do to see you when it's so difficult?

260
00:26:00,980 --> 00:26:03,400
The performance date is so close.

261
00:26:04,950 --> 00:26:08,140
First, accept my glass.

262
00:26:10,850 --> 00:26:18,450
Last week, I went with Father-in-law to a golf meeting, and he asked about you.

263
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:22,400
You should meet with him no matter how busy you are, don't you think so?

264
00:26:23,510 --> 00:26:26,950
He's the bemefactor who put a young guy still wet behind the ears,

265
00:26:26,950 --> 00:26:30,380
having nothing but a body, in such a position.

266
00:26:32,910 --> 00:26:35,540
I'll make some time.

267
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,670
What is all this?

268
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:44,070
I thought you were a prodigy, but I guess you worked hard.

269
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:47,650
You must have practiced so much. The pages are in tatters.

270
00:26:47,650 --> 00:26:50,390
Don't just touch it like that.

271
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:54,200
Hey, are you getting shy?

272
00:26:56,850 --> 00:26:57,860
Saint Saëns Second Concerto in G Minor for Two Pianos

273
00:26:57,860 --> 00:27:00,050
Oh!

274
00:27:00,050 --> 00:27:02,440
Beethoven!

275
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:05,560
I played this so much when I was young.

276
00:27:10,050 --> 00:27:13,250
Can you please play for me just this once?

277
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:14,920
Why should I?

278
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:19,290
Don't be like that. I want to hear it, after a long time.

279
00:27:19,290 --> 00:27:19,950
I don't want to.

280
00:27:19,950 --> 00:27:21,220
Come on, come on, sit down.

281
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:23,760
Sit down, sit down, sit down.

282
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:27,660
Alright! For the music,

283
00:27:27,660 --> 00:27:31,350
I will choose one I like.

284
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:35,920
Für Elise

285
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:22,910
I heard you have Hong Yi Yeong as your assistant.

286
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,990
Yes, well.

287
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:32,920
Hey. You're also someone who's hard to figure out.

288
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:38,160
I feel disgusted whenever I see her, because she reminds me of a dead person.

289
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:40,600
Just what do you intend?

290
00:28:55,990 --> 00:28:58,000
You're Ha Eun Ju, right?

291
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:07,340
For starters, the man in the picture whom you wanted me to investigate

292
00:29:07,340 --> 00:29:11,670
is, like you said, not Jang Yun.

293
00:29:11,670 --> 00:29:17,640
I followed him around to find out his identity and he works part-time at an Italian restaurant.

294
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:22,350
Just in case, I looked into the restaurant and I found something.

295
00:29:22,350 --> 00:29:23,500
What kind of information?

296
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:25,630
Have you perhaps heard of Nano Semi-conductor?  It's a semi-conductor company.

297
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:29,700
- It invested there, in the restaurant.
- Nano Semi-conductor?

298
00:29:29,790 --> 00:29:33,190
Yes. They said the CEO is Jang Seok Hyeon.

299
00:29:33,190 --> 00:29:36,580
By chance, do you know Kim Ian?

300
00:29:36,580 --> 00:29:40,400
That man is Jang Yun's younger brother.

301
00:29:41,990 --> 00:29:44,080
Kim Ian is?

302
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:05,390
Are you watching her or something?

303
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:13,430
Oh, you're here?

304
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:20,300
By the way, you knew each other before, didn't you?

305
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,730
It's been a while.

306
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,400
You had a younger brother?  What did he do?

307
00:31:35,500 --> 00:31:39,400
He was a pianist. Kim Ian.

308
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:42,600
He died a year ago. He was murdered.

309
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:46,870
- Who killed him?
- Someone he loved.

310
00:31:46,900 --> 00:31:50,600
- How is his girlfriend doing?
- She is alive and well.

311
00:31:50,660 --> 00:31:52,640
Then you can go ask her.

312
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,510
Is there a reason why you can't?

313
00:31:55,600 --> 00:32:01,400
Don't you want to know what's in your lost memory?

314
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:22,310
One year ago

315
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:33,500
- What's your name?
- Why my name?

316
00:32:33,550 --> 00:32:38,970
Why are you being that way? When two people first meet, they usually start with their name.

317
00:32:38,970 --> 00:32:41,120
So what's yours?

318
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:44,860
It's Hong Yi Yeong.

319
00:32:44,900 --> 00:32:49,700
Hong Yi Yeong. That's a pretty name.

320
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:54,570
Should I tell you my name too, or not?

321
00:32:55,340 --> 00:32:57,330
I already know yours.

322
00:32:57,330 --> 00:33:00,430
I called your name more than a hundred times today.

323
00:33:00,430 --> 00:33:03,270
Kim Ian. Ian Kim.

324
00:33:04,330 --> 00:33:08,200
Not that name, my real name!

325
00:33:10,630 --> 00:33:14,100
My real name is Jang Yun.

326
00:33:14,100 --> 00:33:18,900
In Dong Jang, Yun Taek Hal, Yun,  Jang Yun.

327
00:33:28,990 --> 00:33:36,640
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

328
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:40,620
♫ My memories that I loved changed ♫

329
00:33:40,620 --> 00:33:44,070
♫ Until I shed all my tears ♫

330
00:33:44,100 --> 00:33:51,330
♫ Even I beg you on my knees, even on my knees, don't hug me ♫

331
00:33:51,330 --> 00:33:54,150
I Wanna Hear Your Song
♫ Even if I have a lot of scars, I'm okay. ♫

332
00:33:54,150 --> 00:33:56,600
Are you afraid that Hong Yi Yeong might remember that day soon?

333
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:59,260
Are you afraid that your beloved cousin might be a murderer?

334
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:00,240
I want to have some fun.

335
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,660
What do you want to do?

336
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:02,560
Date.

337
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,980
An ordinary date.

338
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,930
I heard something weird.

339
00:34:06,930 --> 00:34:09,240
I heard that you are not Jang Yun.

340
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:12,080
When you were a junior, did you take a class with me at Gyeongsang National University?

341
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:15,320
Do you happen to remember the assistant for that class?

342
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:16,830
We're meeting frequently.

343
00:34:16,830 --> 00:34:18,970
I'm thinking of moving into this neighborhood.

344
00:34:18,970 --> 00:34:20,910
I think I like you.

345
00:34:20,910 --> 00:34:22,180
Do you want to date?

346
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:27,800
♫  I call you who has lost your way beyond the sunset ♫
